Extracting Text: Used to pull out specific parts of text from a column
Why Use Text Extract?
 Extract useful parts from longer strings.
 Focus only on the needed portion of a value (e.g., first name from full name, domain from email).
 Helps in cleaning, splitting, and transforming data into usable formats.
To Access Extract: Transform tab → Extract (Dropdown)
Extract Options:
1. Extract First Characters
 Extracts the first N characters from the left.
Example: "Bangalore" → Extract first 3 → "Ban"
Use Case: Get area codes, year (from date string like "2024-05-21")
2. Extract Last Characters
 Extracts the last N characters from the right.
Example: "ABC12345" → Extract last 3 → "345"
Use Case: Get ID suffix, last digits of a code.
3. Extract Range
 Extracts characters starting from a position with a specific length.
Syntax: Start position (0-based) and Number of characters
Example: Text: "Karnataka" Start at 3, length 4 → "nata"
Use Case: Slice specific parts of fixed-format codes.
4. Text Before Delimiter
 Extracts everything before the specified character or symbol.
Example: "john.doe@gmail.com" Delimiter: @ → "john.doe"
Use Case: Get username from an email.
5. Text After Delimiter
 Extracts everything after the specified delimiter.
Example: "john.doe@gmail.com" Delimiter: @ → "gmail.com"
Use Case: Extract domain from email, location from a code.
6. Text Between Delimiters
 Extracts text between two specified delimiters.
Example: "Name[12345]Code" Start: [ , End: ] → "12345"
Use Case: Extract codes, tags, or IDs within brackets or quotes.
